AB  - This paper extends recent studies by deriving sufficient conditions for tariff-immiserization in a small country in the presence of internationally mobile sector-specific capital, the returns of which are taxed or subsidized. Necessary conditions for a welfare-augmenting tariff are also discussed, and the analysis is extended to the welfare implications of changes in the tax or subsidy rate on the earnings of migrating capital.
