AB  - The purpose of this paper is to provide a result on the welfare effect of a transfer, in a general equilibrium exchange model, with no arbitrary restrictions on either the number of commodities traded or the number of countries. Our result can be stated as follows. The donor country is worse off after a transfer, if (a) all goods are ‘net substitutes’ for the donor; (b) all goods are ‘gross substitutes’ for the other countries; and (c) all goods are ‘normal’ for all countries.
