UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199685900224
AB  - This paper uses a two-country model to demonstrate that currency substitution is a channel for the international transmission of monetary disturbances under flexible exchange rates. In the long run, the division of world real wealth and consumption and real exchange rates depend on the growth rates of both monies, but inflation of prices denominated in a particular currency depends only on the rate of growth of that money. In the short run, currency substitution combined with perfect foresight, can be responsible for overshooting in the exchange rate, in both price levels, in real exchange rates, and in national levels of real wealth and consumption.
