AB  - We construct a two-country model in which there exist cash in advance constraints in commodity as well as in asset markets. The seller's currency is used for transactions in commodity markets and the lender's money is used for transactions in the bond markets. The exchange rate equation that emerges from this structure has a new feature — it exhibits a bias towards depreciation of the borrowers' currency. We describe the equilibrium dynamics of this type of a world economy and show that it may exhibit cyclical movements.
